What you need to know:

The duo were awarded for their outstanding performances in athletics that have helped cement Kenya’s sports prowess in the worldFirst, it was the late President Daniel Toroitich arap Moi, who conferred Ndereba with Distinguished Service Medal (DSM) in 2002, before President Mwai Kibaki awarded her the Order of the Grand Warrior of Kenya (OGW) in 2005In 2008, Ndereba was described by Chicago Tribune sportswriter Philip Hersh as the greatest women's marathoner of all time having won two Olympic silver medals.  